      "id": "theory_hex_to_bin",
      "title": "Hex to Binary: Expansion Method",
      "content": "Converting hexadecimal to binary is even easier than binary to hex! Each hex digit simply expands into 4 binary bits.\n\n**The Expansion Method:**\n\n1. Take each hex digit one at a time\n2. Convert each digit to its 4-bit binary equivalent\n3. Combine all the 4-bit groups together\n4. Remove unnecessary leading zeros (optional)\n\n**Quick Reference Table:**\n0 = 0000    4 = 0100    8 = 1000    C = 1100\n1 = 0001    5 = 0101    9 = 1001    D = 1101\n2 = 0010    6 = 0110    A = 1010    E = 1110\n3 = 0011    7 = 0111    B = 1011    F = 1111\n\n**Example 1: Convert 3A to binary**\n\nStep 1: Convert each digit:\n  \u2022 3 = 0011\n  \u2022 A = 1010\nStep 2: Combine: 0011 1010\nResult: 00111010 (or 111010 if you remove leading zeros)\n\n**Example 2: Convert F5 to binary**\n\nStep 1: Convert:\n  \u2022 F = 1111\n  \u2022 5 = 0101\nStep 2: Combine: 1111 0101\nResult: 11110101\n\n**Example 3: Convert 2B8 to binary**\n\nStep 1: Convert each:\n  \u2022 2 = 0010\n  \u2022 B = 1011\n  \u2022 8 = 1000\nStep 2: Combine: 0010 1011 1000\nResult: 001010111000 (or 10101110 00 with spacing)\n\n**Pro Tips:**\n\u2022 Each hex digit ALWAYS becomes exactly 4 bits\n\u2022 Don't forget leading zeros within each group!\n\u2022 For the leftmost hex digit, you can remove leading zeros from the final result\n\u2022 Common values: F=1111, A=1010, 0=0000\n\nThis is the fastest number system conversion because it's just a direct substitution!"
    },
